.TH SMARTMON-SNMP-AGENTXD 8 "2026-05-18" "smartmontools-@PACKAGE_VERSION@" "System Manager's Manual"
.SH NAME
smartmon-snmp-agentxd \- SNMP AgentX subagent for smartmontools SMART data
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smartmon-snmp-agentxd
.RB [ \-c
.IR config ]
.RB [ \-f ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B smartmon-snmp-agentxd
is a net-snmp AgentX subagent (RFC 2741) that exposes SMART drive data
collected by
.BR smartd (8)
via the SMARTMON-* SNMP MIBs.
.PP
It connects to a running
.BR snmpd (8)
master agent over a Unix domain socket, registers the SMARTMON-* OID subtrees,
and responds to SNMP GET/GETNEXT/GETBULK requests.
Trap notifications are sent through the master agent when drive health changes.
.PP
.B smartmon-snmp-agentxd
reads SMART data exclusively from JSON state files written by
.BR smartd (8)
when configured with
.BR \-\-jsonstate .
It does not invoke
.BR smartctl (8)
directly and will not start unless
.B state_dir
is set and smartd has written at least one JSON state file into it.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-c " config"
Path to configuration file.
Default:
.IR @sysconfdir@/smartmontools/snmp-agentxd.conf .
.TP
.B \-f
Run in the foreground; do not daemonise.
Useful for debugging.
.TP
.B \-h
Print usage and exit.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is read from
.I @sysconfdir@/smartmontools/snmp-agentxd.conf
(or the file specified with
.BR \-c ).
.TP
.BI state_dir " path"
.RB ( Required )
Directory where
.BR smartd (8)
writes JSON state files.
Must match the prefix given to smartd's
.B \-\-jsonstate
option.
.TP
.BI agentx_socket " path"
Path to the AgentX master socket.
Must match
.B agentXSocket
in
.IR snmpd.conf (5).
Default:
.IR /var/agentx/master .
.TP
.BI cache_timeout " seconds"
Maximum age of cached SNMP data.
Files not updated for more than
.RI 2\(mu cache_timeout
seconds cause a
.B LOG_WARNING
syslog message.
Default: 300.
.SH SMARTD CONFIGURATION
.BR smartd (8)
must be configured to write JSON state files using the
.B \-x
(extended) flag so that all data required by the MIBs is present,
including NVMe self-test logs and SAS error counter logs.
Add the following to
.IR @sysconfdir@/smartmontools/smartd.conf :
.PP
.RS
.nf
DEVICESCAN -x --jsonstate /run/smartmontools/json/
.fi
.RE
.PP
Using
.B \-a
instead of
.B \-x
omits NVMe self-test log entries and SAS error counters;
those MIB tables will be empty.
.PP
Create the directory beforehand:
.PP
.RS
.nf
mkdir -p /run/smartmontools/json
.fi
.RE
.PP
Restart
.BR smartd (8)
after changing its configuration.
.SH SNMPD CONFIGURATION
Add the following to
.IR /etc/snmp/snmpd.conf :
.PP
.RS
.nf
master agentx
agentXSocket /var/agentx/master
agentXPerms 0660 0660 root netsnmp
mibs +SMARTMON-TC-MIB:SMARTMON-COMMON-MIB:SMARTMON-NVME-MIB:SMARTMON-SATA-MIB:SMARTMON-SAS-MIB
rocommunity public default .1.3.6.1.4.1.99999
.fi
.RE
.SH FILES
.TP
.I @sysconfdir@/smartmontools/snmp-agentxd.conf
Default configuration file.
.TP
.I /run/smartmontools/json/
Recommended location for smartd JSON state files.
.TP
.I /var/agentx/master
Default AgentX master socket.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR smartd (8),
.BR smartd.conf (5),
.BR smartctl (8),
.BR snmpd (8),
.BR snmpd.conf (5)
.SH AUTHORS
smartmontools development team.
See
.I https://www.smartmontools.org/
for details.
